tax cuts from Reagan to Donald Trump, the antitax movement is threatening the nation’s social safety net, increasing inequality, ballooning the national debt, and sapping America’s financial strength. The book chronicles how the movement originated as a fringe enterprise promoted by zealous outsiders using false economic claims and thinly veiled racist rhetoric, and how—abetted by conservative media and Grover Norquist’s “taxpayer protection pledge";—it evolved into a mainstream political force.The important story of how the antitax movement came to dominate and distort politics, and how it impedes rational budgeting, equality, and opportunities, The Power to Destroy is essential reading for understanding American life today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPolitical planningzUnited StatesxEconomic policy. 0aTaxationxMoral and ethical aspectszUnited States. 0aTaxationxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / General.2bisacsh  aFairTax.  aFox News.  aGrover Norquist.  aIRS.  aMichael J. Graetz.  aNewt Gingrich.  aPrinceton University Press.  aProposition 13.  aRonald Reagan.  aRush Limbaugh.  aSocial Security.  aThe Power to Destroy: How the Antitax Movement Hijacked America.  aanti-IRS.  aanti-government.  aanti-tax, antigovernment.  aantitax.  abooks.  aestate tax.  afiscal policy.  afiscal politics.  ahistory of taxation.  aincome tax.  ainequality.  anational debt.  apayroll tax.  apolitical science.  apolitics.  apublic budgets.  arace.  asocial insurance.  asocial movements.  atax policy.  ataxation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311074975540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691225555?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter